cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.RO

This paper deals with the development of an online agent that learns a set of behavioral constraints by observation and uses these learned constraints as a guide when making decisions in an online setting while still being reactive to reward feedback. This involves the use of AI systems that learn through reward feedback about the actions they take, which is a key area of research in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the incorporation of ethical principles and values into the decision-making process, which is relevant to the field of cyber ethics (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper provides a case study with real-world data in two application domains, which suggests a potential application in robotics (cs.RO).
